{"data":{"wordpressPost":{"title":"VoiceOver, tables and visually hiding columns","content":"<html><head></head><body><p>\t\t\t\tI was working more on tables when I ran into another weird issue in VoiceOver. I needed to visually hide a column in a table, but <strong>not</strong> use <code>display: none</code> so that it could still be accessible by screen readers.</p>\n<p>I tried out the <a href=\"http://webaim.org/techniques/css/invisiblecontent/#absolutepositioning\">&#x201C;position content off-screen&#x201D;</a> technique outlined by WebAim.org, and that worked great until I started testing in VoiceOver.</p>\n<p><!--more--></p>\n<p>Shown below is a gif of me navigating through a regular table, and doing the <code>VO + C</code> command to read out the column header. Since I&#x2019;m not hiding anything in the table below, the command worked as expected.</p>\n<p></p><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:66.95238095238096%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/c82464317da1c440669cda61c7f37ec3/79246/before-visually-hiding-column.gif 163w,\n/static/c82464317da1c440669cda61c7f37ec3/669a5/before-visually-hiding-column.gif 325w,\n/static/c82464317da1c440669cda61c7f37ec3/b5c6a/before-visually-hiding-column.gif 650w,\n/static/c82464317da1c440669cda61c7f37ec3/2a9ec/before-visually-hiding-column.gif 975w,\n/static/c82464317da1c440669cda61c7f37ec3/b96f6/before-visually-hiding-column.gif 1050w\" src=\"/static/c82464317da1c440669cda61c7f37ec3/b5c6a/before-visually-hiding-column.gif\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/c82464317da1c440669cda61c7f37ec3/79246/before-visually-hiding-column.gif 163w,\n/static/c82464317da1c440669cda61c7f37ec3/669a5/before-visually-hiding-column.gif 325w,\n/static/c82464317da1c440669cda61c7f37ec3/b5c6a/before-visually-hiding-column.gif 650w,\n/static/c82464317da1c440669cda61c7f37ec3/2a9ec/before-visually-hiding-column.gif 975w,\n/static/c82464317da1c440669cda61c7f37ec3/b96f6/before-visually-hiding-column.gif 1050w\" src=\"/static/c82464317da1c440669cda61c7f37ec3/b5c6a/before-visually-hiding-column.gif\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div><p></p>\n<p>Next, I visually hid a column and then tried the same command. I could navigate every cell in the hidden column just fine, but when I did <code>VO + C</code>, it would  <strong>read the header of the column immediately next to it</strong>. Notice how in the gif below, it reads &#x201C;Column 2&#x201D; instead of &#x201C;Column 1&#x201D; even though I&#x2019;m focused on the first column.</p>\n<p></p><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:66.95238095238096%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/c7f25e4ee9fee7f0986bf54be18fed6a/79246/after-visually-hiding-column.gif 163w,\n/static/c7f25e4ee9fee7f0986bf54be18fed6a/669a5/after-visually-hiding-column.gif 325w,\n/static/c7f25e4ee9fee7f0986bf54be18fed6a/b5c6a/after-visually-hiding-column.gif 650w,\n/static/c7f25e4ee9fee7f0986bf54be18fed6a/2a9ec/after-visually-hiding-column.gif 975w,\n/static/c7f25e4ee9fee7f0986bf54be18fed6a/b96f6/after-visually-hiding-column.gif 1050w\" src=\"/static/c7f25e4ee9fee7f0986bf54be18fed6a/b5c6a/after-visually-hiding-column.gif\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/c7f25e4ee9fee7f0986bf54be18fed6a/79246/after-visually-hiding-column.gif 163w,\n/static/c7f25e4ee9fee7f0986bf54be18fed6a/669a5/after-visually-hiding-column.gif 325w,\n/static/c7f25e4ee9fee7f0986bf54be18fed6a/b5c6a/after-visually-hiding-column.gif 650w,\n/static/c7f25e4ee9fee7f0986bf54be18fed6a/2a9ec/after-visually-hiding-column.gif 975w,\n/static/c7f25e4ee9fee7f0986bf54be18fed6a/b96f6/after-visually-hiding-column.gif 1050w\" src=\"/static/c7f25e4ee9fee7f0986bf54be18fed6a/b5c6a/after-visually-hiding-column.gif\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div><p></p>\n<p>I guess the lesson here is to be very thorough when testing for accessibility, and to not forget about <a href=\"https://www.apple.com/voiceover/info/guide/_1131.html\">keyboard commands</a>. I imagine it&#x2019;d be pretty frustrating and disorienting for a screen reader user if they are not able to quickly tell which column they are on.</p>\n<h3>What did I do instead?</h3>\n<p>To get around this, I ended up using <code>text-indent: -9999px</code> to move the text off-screen. Doing this did not break the <code>VO + C</code> command. You can see in the gif below that the proper table header is read in the first column.</p>\n<p></p><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:66.95238095238096%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/4ad32cbb08d3ed959a83f0cdb39136b7/79246/text-indenting-columns.gif 163w,\n/static/4ad32cbb08d3ed959a83f0cdb39136b7/669a5/text-indenting-columns.gif 325w,\n/static/4ad32cbb08d3ed959a83f0cdb39136b7/b5c6a/text-indenting-columns.gif 650w,\n/static/4ad32cbb08d3ed959a83f0cdb39136b7/2a9ec/text-indenting-columns.gif 975w,\n/static/4ad32cbb08d3ed959a83f0cdb39136b7/b96f6/text-indenting-columns.gif 1050w\" src=\"/static/4ad32cbb08d3ed959a83f0cdb39136b7/b5c6a/text-indenting-columns.gif\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/4ad32cbb08d3ed959a83f0cdb39136b7/79246/text-indenting-columns.gif 163w,\n/static/4ad32cbb08d3ed959a83f0cdb39136b7/669a5/text-indenting-columns.gif 325w,\n/static/4ad32cbb08d3ed959a83f0cdb39136b7/b5c6a/text-indenting-columns.gif 650w,\n/static/4ad32cbb08d3ed959a83f0cdb39136b7/2a9ec/text-indenting-columns.gif 975w,\n/static/4ad32cbb08d3ed959a83f0cdb39136b7/b96f6/text-indenting-columns.gif 1050w\" src=\"/static/4ad32cbb08d3ed959a83f0cdb39136b7/b5c6a/text-indenting-columns.gif\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div><p></p>\n<p>Now this technique still preserves the width of the column, but in my case this was okay because I was overlaying another table on top of where the empty space is (more on that in a future blog post!).</p>\n<h3>Codepen Demo</h3>\n<p data-height=\"331\" data-theme-id=\"0\" data-slug-hash=\"dGrzrP\" data-default-tab=\"result\" data-user=\"tetchi\" class=\"codepen\">See the Pen <a href=\"http://codepen.io/tetchi/pen/dGrzrP/\">Visually hiding a column</a> by Tetsuro Takara (<a href=\"http://codepen.io/tetchi\">@tetchi</a>) on <a href=\"http://codepen.io\">CodePen</a>.</p>\n<p><script async src=\"//assets.codepen.io/assets/embed/ei.js\"></script>\t\t</p>\n</body></html>","wordpress_id":4777},"allWordpressWpComments":{"edges":[]}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"a11y-tables-and-visually-hiding-columns","wordpressId":4777,"newerPostSlug":"accessibility-improvements-to-my-blog","olderPostSlug":"japan-trip-2015-conclusion"}}